HEADWORD: briary
<hw>briary</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having or covered with
protective barbs or quills or spines or thorns etc.; -- of plants or
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> barbed, barbellate, briery, bristly, burred, burry,
prickly, spiny, thorny.</syn>⟦br⟧
